<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="137" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Defense Files: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                                Commander in Chief, Allied Forces, North Africa</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EDD1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Eisenhower</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d137fn1">Sent to
                                Malta via Navy channels.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">ultra secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Aboard
                                        the</hi> U. S. S. “<hi rend="smallcaps">Iowa</hi>”</placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-17">17 Nov[ember 19]43</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>From Com[mander] in Ch[ief] Embarked.</p>
                        <p>Transmit to <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval
                                Person</gloss>[:] “Official information from Washington to effect
                            that meeting place is known to enemy through press and radio. Propose
                            meeting place be changed to Khartoum[.] “Confirm seriousness of leak.
                            Adjust transit as you deem requisite.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>